Macro Bank Inc. (NYSE:BMA) Downgraded by Zacks Investment Research


					Posted by Lucas Kauffman on Jul 19th, 2017 // No Comments




Zacks Investment Research lowered shares of Macro Bank Inc. (NYSE:BMA) from a buy rating to a hold rating in a research report released on Wednesday, June 21st. 
According to Zacks, “Banco Macro Bansud is a leading bank in Argentina. With the most extensive private-sector branch network in the country, Banco Marco provides standard banking products and services to a nationwide customer base.   “


 Get Macro Bank Inc. alerts:



Separately, Credit Suisse Group raised shares of Macro Bank from a neutral rating to an outperform rating in a research note on Tuesday, June 13th. One research analyst  has rated the stock with a hold rating and four have issued  a buy rating to the stock. The company currently has a consensus rating of Buy and an average target price of $92.75.





Shares of Macro Bank (NYSE BMA) opened at 86.00 on Wednesday. Macro Bank has a 52-week low of $61.12 and a 52-week high of $97.86. The company’s 50-day moving average price is $89.97 and its 200-day moving average price is $84.26. The firm has a market cap of $50.27 billion, a PE ratio of 120.28 and a beta of 1.41. 
COPYRIGHT VIOLATION NOTICE: “Macro Bank Inc. (NYSE:BMA) Downgraded by Zacks Investment Research” was  reported by Chaffey Breeze and is the sole property of of Chaffey Breeze. If you are reading this story on another website, it was illegally stolen and republished in violation of US and international trademark & copyright laws. The correct version of this story can be read at https://www.chaffeybreeze.com/2017/07/19/zacks-investment-research-downgrades-macro-bank-inc-bma-to-hold-updated-updated-updated.html. 
The business also recently announced a … dividend, which was paid on Friday, June 23rd. Investors of record on Friday, June 16th were paid a $0.002 dividend. This represents a yield of 0.86%. The ex-dividend date  was Wednesday, June 14th. Macro Bank’s payout ratio is presently 19.92%. 
A number of institutional investors have recently made changes to their positions in the company. Genesis Asset Managers LLP increased its position in  Macro Bank by 13.4% in the second quarter. Genesis Asset Managers LLP now owns 1,155,491 shares of the bank’s stock valued at $106,525,000 after buying an additional 136,358 shares in the last quarter.  William Blair Investment Management LLC boosted its stake in shares of  Macro Bank by 31.3% in the first quarter. William Blair Investment Management LLC now owns 406,520 shares of the bank’s stock valued at $35,245,000 after buying an additional 96,884 shares during the last quarter.  Franklin Resources Inc. boosted its stake in shares of  Macro Bank by 129.0% in the fourth quarter. Franklin Resources Inc. now owns 350,168 shares of the bank’s stock valued at $22,534,000 after buying an additional 197,249 shares during the last quarter.  Goldman Sachs Group Inc. boosted its stake in shares of  Macro Bank by 32.7% in the first quarter. Goldman Sachs Group Inc. now owns 290,159 shares of the bank’s stock valued at $25,157,000 after buying an additional 71,558 shares during the last quarter.  Finally, Russell Investments Group Ltd. boosted its stake in shares of  Macro Bank by 4.2% in the first quarter. Russell Investments Group Ltd. now owns 220,418 shares of the bank’s stock valued at $19,109,000 after buying an additional 8,958 shares during the last quarter. 23.28% of the stock is owned by hedge funds and other institutional investors. 
Macro Bank Company Profile
Banco Macro SA is an Argnetina-based financial institution (the Bank) that offers traditional bank products and services to companies, including those operating in regional economies, as well as to individuals. In addition, the Bank performs certain transactions through its subsidiaries, including mainly Banco del Tucuman, Macro Bank Ltd, Macro Securities SA, Macro Fiducia SA and Macro Fondos SGFCI SA.
