Short Interest in Macro Bank Inc. (BMA) Declines By 50.2%

					Posted by Candace Mills on Jul 20th, 2017 // No Comments 



Macro Bank Inc. (NYSE:BMA) was the target of a significant decline in short interest during the month of June. As of June 30th, there was short interest totalling 290,942 shares,  a decline of 50.2% from the June 15th total of 584,685 shares. Based on an average daily volume of 422,362 shares, the days-to-cover ratio is currently 0.7 days. 
Macro Bank (NYSE BMA) opened at 87.47 on Thursday. The firm’s 50 day moving average is $89.97 and its 200 day moving average is $84.26. Macro Bank has a 1-year low of $61.12 and a 1-year high of $97.86. The stock has a market capitalization of $51.13 billion, a P/E ratio of 125.68 and a beta of 1.41. 


 Get Macro Bank Inc. alerts:



The firm also recently declared a … dividend, which was paid on Friday, June 23rd. Shareholders of record on Friday, June 16th were paid a $0.002 dividend. The ex-dividend date  was Wednesday, June 14th. This represents a yield of 0.86%. Macro Bank’s payout ratio is 19.92%. 




A number of hedge funds and other institutional investors have recently bought and sold shares of the company. Renaissance Technologies LLC increased its position in  Macro Bank by 278.7% in the fourth quarter. Renaissance Technologies LLC now owns 82,500 shares of the bank’s stock valued at $5,309,000 after buying an additional 60,715 shares during the last quarter.  Quadrature Capital Ltd purchased a new position in  Macro Bank during the fourth quarter worth approximately $418,000.  Manning & Napier Advisors LLC purchased a new position in  Macro Bank during the first quarter worth approximately $3,682,000.  Rothschild Investment Corp IL purchased a new position in  Macro Bank during the first quarter worth approximately $206,000.  Finally, Nationwide Fund Advisors increased its position in  Macro Bank by 24.1% in the first quarter. Nationwide Fund Advisors now owns 67,000 shares of the bank’s stock worth $5,809,000 after buying an additional 13,000 shares in the last quarter. Institutional investors and hedge funds own  23.28% of the company’s stock. 
Several equities research analysts have issued reports on the stock. Zacks Investment Research lowered shares of Macro Bank from a “buy” rating to a “hold” rating in a research report on Tuesday, June 6th. Credit Suisse Group upgraded shares of Macro Bank from a “neutral” rating to an “outperform” rating in a research report on Tuesday, June 13th. One investment analyst  has rated the stock with a hold rating and four have issued  a buy rating to the stock. The stock currently has a consensus rating of “Buy” and a consensus price target of $92.75.
WARNING: “Short Interest in Macro Bank Inc. (BMA) Declines By 50.2%” was originally  posted by StockNewsTimes and is the property of of StockNewsTimes. If you are reading this piece of content on another website, it was illegally copied and republished in violation of United States and international trademark & copyright law. The original version of this piece of content can be read at https://stocknewstimes.com/2017/07/20/short-interest-in-macro-bank-inc-bma-declines-by-50-2.html. 
About Macro Bank
Banco Macro SA is an Argnetina-based financial institution (the Bank) that offers traditional bank products and services to companies, including those operating in regional economies, as well as to individuals. In addition, the Bank performs certain transactions through its subsidiaries, including mainly Banco del Tucuman, Macro Bank Ltd, Macro Securities SA, Macro Fiducia SA and Macro Fondos SGFCI SA.






